Function Reference/comment author link « WordPress Codex
-----------

Displays the comment author's name linked to his/her
[URL](/Glossary#URI_and_URL "Glossary"), if one was provided.

Use
[get\_comment\_author\_link](/Template_Tags/get_comment_author_link "Template Tags/get comment author link")
to retrieve the value.

Usage
-----

`  <?php comment_author_link( $comment_ID ); ?> `

Example
-------

    <p>Comment by: <?php comment_author_link(); ?></p>

Parameters
----------

 `comment_ID` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The ID of the comment for which to print the author's
    link.
    Default: 0 (the current comment)

Changelog
---------

-    ? : Added the 'comment\_ID' parameter.
-   Since: 0.71

